To calculate area of rectangle user will be prompted to enter the length and width of a rectangle using nextDouble() method of Scanner class.
This length and width of a rectangle values are stored in variables “length” and “width” of data type double. 
Then using above user entered values we calculate area of rectangle using below formula,

calculate rectangle area = length * width

Here's the java program.

import java.util.Scanner;
public class RectangleArea
{
   public static void main(String[] args)
   {
      Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
      System.out.println("Please enter length of rectangle: ");
      double length = sc.nextDouble();
      System.out.println("Please enter width of rectangle: ");
      double width = sc.nextDouble();
      double area = length * width;
      System.out.println("Area of rectangle is: " + area);
      sc.close();
   }
}

Output:

Please enter length of rectangle: 2
Please enter width of rectangle: 5
Area of rectangle is: 10.0

Above program can be executed without using Scanner class

class RectangleArea
{
   public static void main (String[] args)
   {
      double length = 2.0;
      double width = 5.0;
      double area = length * width;
      System.out.println("Area of rectangle is: " + area);
   }
}

Output:

Area of rectangle is: 10.0

